== Input Method Related ==

	* [http://www.openi18n.org/subgroups/im/IIIMF/ IIIMF]  Internet/Intranet Input Method Framework.
	* [http://uim.freedesktop.org UIM]	is a library to support input many languages.
	* [http://immodule-qt.freedesktop.org/ Qt-immodule] Immodule support in Qt (in progress).

Come to join us to discuss [http://www.kde.gr.jp/~daisuke/immodule''for''qt/pukiwiki/?ImmoduleForQt4RequirementsDocument what should be incorporated] into Qt4 in terms of built-in qt-immodule support.

== Other Input Method Implementation ==

	* [http://www.csie.nctu.edu.tw/~cp76/gcin/ gcin] (Chinese) is a traditional Chinese zhuyin input method.
	* [http://jserv.sayya.org/wiki/index.php/Qooing Qooing] (Chinese) is a library for chewing (similar to zhuyin) input method.

== Other Things about Complex Input ==

	* [http://wauug.erols.com/~balsa/linux/deadkeys/ Dead Keys Controversy] provides information on using international character sets under Linux and particularly under X11R6.

